WEBVTT

00:13.103 --> 00:15.107
GUARD: You're going
to be side by side

00:15.107 --> 00:16.108
all the way to Australia.

00:16.743 --> 00:17.679
ESTELLA: I intend
to find a rich man,

00:17.679 --> 00:19.750
have him take me
as from here as I can go.

00:19.750 --> 00:21.119
Cairo looks nice.

00:21.119 --> 00:22.120
Could you take me to Cairo?

00:22.655 --> 00:24.158
- ESTELLA: Herbert.
- Will you just stop?

00:30.103 --> 00:31.607
MISS HAVISHAM: <i>So, Pip,
are you in love with her yet?</i>

00:32.810 --> 00:34.713
PIP: <i>I told you, my intention
is not to fall in love.</i>

00:35.481 --> 00:37.217
MISS HAVISHAM: <i>Love is not
always the result of intention.</i>

00:39.121 --> 00:40.357
<i>Do you love her?</i>

00:44.566 --> 00:45.769
(WHISPERS) Oh, Pip.

00:45.769 --> 00:46.771
MR. PUMBLECHOOK:
<i>She conducts her business</i>

00:46.771 --> 00:49.074
<i>through a Mr. Jaggers.
He's King's counsel.</i>

00:51.412 --> 00:52.281
Your signature,

00:52.849 --> 00:53.784
or your shame.

00:54.753 --> 00:57.224
Miss Havisham says to tell you
that your education is over.

00:58.594 --> 00:59.763
Estella, no, no.

00:59.763 --> 01:01.399
Estella, Estella, stop.

01:02.569 --> 01:03.403
I'm in love with you.

01:06.844 --> 01:11.218
I am looking for a boy
by the name of Pip Gargery.

01:37.605 --> 01:38.540
(HORSE HUFFS)

01:56.744 --> 01:58.446
(WOMAN LAUGHING IN DISTANCE)

02:04.191 --> 02:05.427
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

02:06.597 --> 02:07.532
(EXHALES)

02:24.265 --> 02:25.568
(WOMAN LAUGHING)

02:30.545 --> 02:31.680
(GASPS)

02:31.680 --> 02:33.483
MR. JAGGERS:
Ladies and gentlemen,

02:33.483 --> 02:36.824
who among you wasn't just
as foolish at this age?

02:36.824 --> 02:38.627
You take your
fucking hands off me.

02:41.399 --> 02:44.606
I was sent by Miss Havisham
and Miss Estella.

02:45.541 --> 02:46.710
Let's go somewhere quiet.

03:26.957 --> 03:28.527
That rum is
on my father's slate.

03:29.663 --> 03:33.369
Nothing in your life is any more
on your father's slate.

03:34.606 --> 03:36.009
From this moment on,
everything in your life

03:36.009 --> 03:37.277
is on my slate.

03:39.583 --> 03:40.450
Who are you?

03:42.054 --> 03:44.492
The mouth of the Thames
tastes the best rum,

03:45.595 --> 03:47.264
but you marshland savages
drink it all

03:47.264 --> 03:48.433
before it gets to London.

03:48.902 --> 03:50.671
- How do you know Miss Estella?
- (CHUCKLES)

03:52.341 --> 03:54.278
Did you ever go hunting
sparrows in the fog?

03:55.046 --> 03:55.948
Boy, look at me.

03:57.384 --> 03:58.787
I swear to God,
I will get an answer.

03:59.455 --> 04:00.423
(CHUCKLES)

04:00.758 --> 04:02.394
Who are you?

04:02.662 --> 04:04.699
He has the ear of God.

04:08.774 --> 04:10.878
The knife came as a gift
with this brand new suit.

04:12.615 --> 04:13.617
It slips into the boot.

04:15.521 --> 04:17.658
A knife such as gentlemen carry.

04:19.996 --> 04:20.831
I asked you a fucking que...

04:21.733 --> 04:22.602
(OBJECTS CLATTERING)

04:26.643 --> 04:29.949
Not actually a knife
such as gentlemen carry, Pip.

04:31.385 --> 04:33.289
Soon, you will learn
to tell the difference.

04:39.101 --> 04:41.740
If you want to defend yourself
with a knife made of tin,

04:41.740 --> 04:43.376
try it, by all means.

04:43.811 --> 04:46.883
But if you want £5,000,

04:48.386 --> 04:50.090
an apartment
in the heart of London,

04:50.090 --> 04:52.027
a position in my practice,

04:52.929 --> 04:55.601
and a pathway to the heart
of the girl you love...

04:56.402 --> 04:59.474
If you want all of those things,
as I know you surely do...

05:00.076 --> 05:01.613
Sit down, Pip.

05:09.061 --> 05:12.400
Now, I know you can read,

05:13.402 --> 05:15.808
so you will see the sum is drawn
for my company account.

05:18.714 --> 05:20.651
The true identity
of your benefactor

05:21.452 --> 05:23.089
is to remain a secret

05:23.089 --> 05:25.661
at the insistence
of the benefactor.

05:27.699 --> 05:29.402
Who else on Earth
other than Miss Havisham

05:29.402 --> 05:30.504
would give me such a sum?

05:32.140 --> 05:33.777
The Earth is a big place, Pip.

05:35.080 --> 05:36.650
That you will learn.

05:37.519 --> 05:39.522
You will learn it
because I will teach you.

05:42.729 --> 05:43.697
Teach me what?

05:46.870 --> 05:48.674
Teach you first to be a rat,

05:50.443 --> 05:51.546
then a snake,

05:52.849 --> 05:54.051
then a vulture

05:55.788 --> 05:57.892
and then, with blood
dripping from your beak,

05:59.696 --> 06:01.666
I will teach you
how to be a gentleman.

06:06.442 --> 06:07.545
But now the night is cold.

06:10.483 --> 06:11.754
I suggest you take
a swig of this

06:11.754 --> 06:13.422
before we mount up and ride.

06:14.893 --> 06:16.897
- Ride at this hour?
- Yes.

06:16.897 --> 06:18.700
We have urgent business
in London.

06:19.903 --> 06:21.607
Come.

06:21.607 --> 06:23.611
(STAMMERING) I need to gather
my things and say goodbye.

06:23.611 --> 06:24.612
No.

06:25.447 --> 06:27.752
- My sister...
- Your sister and her blacksmith

06:27.752 --> 06:29.488
will wake to find a check
of compensation

06:29.488 --> 06:30.456
on their doorstep.

06:32.729 --> 06:33.998
There is a girl who
deserves explanation...

06:33.998 --> 06:35.534
There is a girl called Biddy.

06:36.235 --> 06:37.972
And she is of no consequence.

06:38.306 --> 06:39.575
Not at all.

06:40.911 --> 06:42.615
The moment has come, Pip.

06:43.016 --> 06:45.453
The most important moment
of your life.

06:46.122 --> 06:49.027
Either you come with me now
or give me back the check.

06:55.541 --> 06:56.576
You have ten seconds.

06:58.947 --> 07:00.718
(CHURCH BELL TOLLING)

07:06.963 --> 07:10.036
Will you allow
that same old church bell

07:10.337 --> 07:12.708
to peel away your whole life,

07:13.042 --> 07:15.113
hour after hour?

07:23.997 --> 07:25.233
I will write my explanations.

07:25.233 --> 07:26.804
Yes.

07:26.804 --> 07:29.108
And the next time you see
any of the poor people

07:29.108 --> 07:31.078
from this
miserable little village,

07:31.613 --> 07:34.085
you'll be looking down on them

07:34.085 --> 07:37.725
from a very, very great height.

08:23.851 --> 08:24.819
Come on, Pip.

08:25.754 --> 08:27.090
I like to ride quickly.

08:27.592 --> 08:28.794
As if the Devil were chasing me.

09:10.678 --> 09:12.013
(HORSES WHINNYING)

09:38.099 --> 09:39.367
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

09:58.005 --> 09:59.942
(CHATTER CONTINUES)

10:08.259 --> 10:09.962
Your horses appear
not to need rest.

10:10.864 --> 10:12.000
Yes.

10:12.434 --> 10:15.240
I start them young,
worked them hard,

10:15.240 --> 10:16.108
as I will with you.

10:19.749 --> 10:21.218
I will give my horse a rest.

10:29.802 --> 10:30.804
Thank you.

10:46.068 --> 10:49.274
Pip, you should know, in London,
horse troughs are mostly piss.

11:07.043 --> 11:08.881
Having spent nine hours
on a muddy road with you,

11:08.881 --> 11:09.849
I am curious.

11:12.220 --> 11:14.291
Why did my mysterious benefactor
think it wise

11:14.291 --> 11:16.128
to make a man like you
my guardian?

11:16.763 --> 11:18.198
Because I am known to be evil.

11:19.802 --> 11:20.938
Celebrated for it.

11:22.207 --> 11:23.476
And your benefactor knows

11:23.476 --> 11:24.879
that in an evil place
like London,

11:25.948 --> 11:27.885
attachment to virtue
would be fatal.

11:31.225 --> 11:32.795
You mentioned an apartment.
I need to rest.

11:33.262 --> 11:34.297
No.

11:34.966 --> 11:36.736
You will rest in your grave
and not before.

11:46.422 --> 11:48.425
I hope your new boots
are waterproof.

11:50.229 --> 11:51.799
We are walking through water?

11:52.968 --> 11:54.037
No.

11:54.438 --> 11:56.208
We'll be walking
into our appointment

11:56.208 --> 11:57.310
through rivers of blood.

11:58.446 --> 12:00.049
(PIG SQUEALING)

12:17.852 --> 12:19.822
There, Pip.
Our business is at hand.

12:31.412 --> 12:32.948
Central Court.

12:33.517 --> 12:35.152
Chief Justice's office.

12:36.055 --> 12:37.223
The doors will be unlocked.

12:39.862 --> 12:41.799
Leave the beastly business
to me, Mr. Jaggers.

12:57.898 --> 12:59.268
MAN 1: Mr. Jaggers, sir!

12:59.268 --> 13:00.938
- MAN 2: Sir, please.
- WOMAN: Mr. Jaggers, I beg you.

13:00.938 --> 13:02.407
My son has been
convicted wrongly

13:02.407 --> 13:04.444
on the word of a watchman
who coveted my daughter.

13:04.913 --> 13:06.550
I take no petitions
outside of my chambers.

13:06.550 --> 13:07.851
Please, Mr. Jaggers.

13:13.630 --> 13:15.166
Boy, you'd be better
letting it out

13:15.166 --> 13:16.268
than swallowing it down.

13:17.905 --> 13:19.007
Because the horrors
of this morning

13:19.007 --> 13:20.109
have only just begun.

13:38.513 --> 13:40.149
I have in my hand three keys.

13:41.553 --> 13:42.888
This is the first of them.

13:43.990 --> 13:45.093
It is the key to the door

13:45.093 --> 13:46.529
of the outer perimeter
of the Old Bailey.

13:48.232 --> 13:50.169
I read that within these walls,
only blind justice prevails.

13:51.472 --> 13:52.473
Oh, Pip.

13:53.242 --> 13:55.479
Your awakening will be
truly heart-wrenching.

14:15.119 --> 14:17.591
It's not just the history
of the place that impresses.

14:17.858 --> 14:19.427
It is the spirit of dread.

14:20.964 --> 14:22.568
The joy of reprieve,

14:23.002 --> 14:24.905
the horror
of the death sentence,

14:25.439 --> 14:27.243
which makes the hairs
stand on end.

14:34.592 --> 14:38.299
Prepare yourself, Pip,
for your first practical lesson

14:38.299 --> 14:40.236
in the wicked ways
of this wicked city.

14:43.409 --> 14:44.277
PIP: Dear God.

14:47.618 --> 14:48.553
MR. JAGGERS: Yes.

14:49.689 --> 14:50.690
"Dear God."

14:55.132 --> 14:56.602
Was Chief Justice.

14:59.140 --> 15:01.344
One of the four most powerful
in the Bailey

15:03.550 --> 15:07.089
Over these past years,
he has been of great use to me.

15:09.294 --> 15:10.664
You knew he was here hanging?

15:11.164 --> 15:12.099
Yes.

15:13.469 --> 15:15.640
I came yesterday forenoon
and found him.

15:16.642 --> 15:19.414
But I had business.
Fetching you from the marshes,

15:25.159 --> 15:26.161
(VOMITING)

15:30.771 --> 15:33.108
- (OPENS DRAWER)
- MR. JAGGERS: Ah.

15:34.477 --> 15:35.412
Why didn't you tell someone?

15:37.718 --> 15:39.588
Because I need the old man
to sign some papers.

15:40.724 --> 15:42.026
Petitions for pardon.

15:44.064 --> 15:46.201
These are the last two he will
ever be able to help me with.

15:46.736 --> 15:47.671
Alas.

15:52.748 --> 15:54.552
You will forge the signature
of a dead man?

15:55.754 --> 15:56.689
Yeah.

15:58.727 --> 15:59.662
Like so.

16:04.337 --> 16:05.339
And so.

16:06.743 --> 16:08.546
With the steady hand
of a painter.

16:13.489 --> 16:17.063
And in case his absence
from any subsequent inquiry

16:17.831 --> 16:20.202
leads to questions of veracity,

16:20.837 --> 16:22.741
I will also need the signature
of a witness.

16:28.385 --> 16:29.320
My young Pip.

16:34.565 --> 16:37.036
An honest boy from the marshes,

16:37.805 --> 16:39.676
who saw with his own two eyes,

16:39.676 --> 16:43.215
the old Judge sign
these petitions for pardon

16:43.783 --> 16:45.319
at precisely...

16:46.121 --> 16:47.624
5:35 in the a.m.

17:00.449 --> 17:03.255
Nine hours ago I was drunk
in The Three Jolly Bargemen.

17:03.557 --> 17:05.226
And now...

17:05.226 --> 17:07.463
And now you are in the world
of gentlemen and commerce.

17:08.667 --> 17:10.369
Your earnest wish
come true, yes?

17:14.845 --> 17:16.282
By signing the parchment,

17:16.282 --> 17:18.252
you will be saving
the lives of two men.

17:23.162 --> 17:24.498
- Men who are innocent, yes?
- Oh, Pip.

17:24.832 --> 17:26.268
I'm a lawyer.

17:26.268 --> 17:27.771
Innocence and guilt
are not my concern.

17:30.744 --> 17:32.313
I have read books about...

17:33.248 --> 17:34.250
about murder.

17:34.618 --> 17:35.820
It's not murder. It's suicide.

17:37.624 --> 17:38.693
When they find the body hanging,

17:38.693 --> 17:40.664
they will be able to tell
how long he's been dead.

17:40.664 --> 17:41.799
They will not find
the body hanging.

17:42.333 --> 17:43.670
The butcher we met
in the meat market

17:43.670 --> 17:44.772
is coming to collect it.

17:49.447 --> 17:50.517
Sign the parchment.

18:31.364 --> 18:34.370
Not yet 6:00,
and already a profit of £20.

18:35.507 --> 18:36.441
Come.

18:56.849 --> 18:58.653
MAN 1: Mr. Jaggers, please.
You're my only hope, sir.

18:59.154 --> 19:02.227
- Please, just listen to me.
- MAN 2: Please.

19:02.227 --> 19:03.863
MAN 3: Mr. Jaggers,
did my wife speak to you?

19:05.399 --> 19:08.239
Our only son hangs
at Newgate tomorrow.

19:08.239 --> 19:09.642
(KNOCKING ON DOOR LOUDLY)

19:09.642 --> 19:11.311
Yes, sir. I think she did.

19:11.311 --> 19:12.614
MR. JAGGERS: You. Hush.

19:13.482 --> 19:15.721
Mr. Jaggers, you said
if we raised, uh, £10...

19:15.721 --> 19:17.624
Pip, you do not speak
unless you are being paid.

19:18.158 --> 19:20.564
We've raised, uh,
£7 and four shillings.

19:20.564 --> 19:23.235
Penny a word, farthing a pause,
halfpenny for a raised eyebrow.

19:23.235 --> 19:24.906
He's only 15 years old,
Mr. Jaggers.

19:24.906 --> 19:26.509
- (RESUMES KNOCKING)
- Sir!

19:26.509 --> 19:27.476
MAN 3: In the name of God...

19:30.282 --> 19:31.284
In the name of who?

19:31.586 --> 19:32.486
(DOOR UNLOCKS)

19:34.925 --> 19:38.599
Please, please appeal
to Mr. Jagger's heart.

19:39.902 --> 19:40.904
Hmm?

19:41.238 --> 19:42.741
- (CLAMORING)
- MAN: Sir, please!

19:42.741 --> 19:43.910
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

19:59.440 --> 20:00.510
Mr. Jaggers?

20:02.781 --> 20:03.783
Mr. Jaggers?

20:04.284 --> 20:06.488
Be frugal with words here, Pip.

20:07.558 --> 20:10.329
Spend them like gold sovereigns.

20:12.668 --> 20:15.540
Mr. Jaggers, that man outside
in need of £2 and 16 shillings.

20:17.578 --> 20:18.847
Since I am now quite wealthy,

20:18.847 --> 20:20.316
I'd be happy
to give him that amount

20:20.316 --> 20:21.752
to save his son
from the gallows.

20:28.432 --> 20:29.535
Give me the check.

20:38.720 --> 20:40.456
It is such a small amount
compared to this, Mr...

20:40.456 --> 20:41.424
Pip.

20:43.696 --> 20:45.533
There. Pity.

20:46.234 --> 20:47.538
- Compassion.
- Mr. Jaggers, sir,

20:47.538 --> 20:48.607
I spoke out of weariness.

20:48.607 --> 20:49.675
Empathy.

20:49.909 --> 20:51.579
Charity.

20:51.579 --> 20:52.814
And the worst of all,
the unkindest cut of all,

20:53.516 --> 20:55.385
- kindness.
- No, please, please.

20:55.854 --> 20:56.989
Mr. Jaggers.

20:58.358 --> 20:59.795
Please, I won't make
such a suggestion again.

21:01.031 --> 21:03.503
I will explain to Mr. Rutherford
at the bank

21:04.338 --> 21:07.745
the check was damaged
in the pursuit of the education

21:07.745 --> 21:10.950
of a poor young boy
from the provinces.

21:15.660 --> 21:16.896
Mr. Jaggers,
I'm not thinking properly,

21:16.896 --> 21:17.864
Hmm.

21:19.802 --> 21:23.576
It has been a very...
eventful day.

21:25.012 --> 21:26.314
And a half.

21:28.418 --> 21:30.990
And I really,
really need to rest.

21:32.527 --> 21:34.765
My assistant, Mr. Wemmick,
will be here shortly

21:34.765 --> 21:36.334
to take you to your apartment.

21:37.403 --> 21:38.739
I have left
suitable clothing there.

21:40.075 --> 21:41.879
He will have you change
and then return.

21:42.715 --> 21:45.954
When you get back here,
you can begin work, copying.

21:51.899 --> 21:52.767
Where are you going?

21:53.670 --> 21:54.771
To save the lives of two men

21:55.607 --> 21:57.844
and to find a replacement
for the hanging judge.

22:07.798 --> 22:08.733
Father...

22:13.408 --> 22:15.780
Mr. Jaggers has made me believe
London is a very wicked place.

22:16.081 --> 22:17.785
(CHUCKLES)

22:17.785 --> 22:20.489
Well, you may get cheated,
robbed and murdered in London,

22:20.489 --> 22:22.494
but there are plenty of people
anywhere who do that for you.

22:23.963 --> 22:25.365
Only if there is bad blood.

22:26.602 --> 22:28.405
There's not much bad blood.

22:29.508 --> 22:31.545
They'll do it, if there's
anything to be got by it.

22:33.215 --> 22:34.083
That makes it worse.

22:35.486 --> 22:36.421
You think so?

22:37.591 --> 22:38.793
Much about the same,
I would say.

22:39.695 --> 22:42.568
Mr. Wemmick, you seem
to be very plain-speaking.

22:42.568 --> 22:45.506
And there is a question
I really need a plain answer to.

22:46.341 --> 22:48.680
It is not unusual
for a wealthy benefactor

22:48.680 --> 22:51.484
to wish to remain anonymous,
and that is how it will stay.

22:52.854 --> 22:53.923
But you know who it is.

22:54.190 --> 22:55.092
No, I do not.

22:56.896 --> 22:58.098
You've heard of a Miss Havisham?

22:58.866 --> 22:59.935
Indeed, I have.

23:00.302 --> 23:02.006
And a Miss Estella?

23:02.006 --> 23:03.843
Actually, it was I
who drew up the papers

23:03.843 --> 23:06.447
for Miss Estella's
legal adoption 18 years ago.

23:08.753 --> 23:09.921
Does Miss Estella
ever come here?

23:11.057 --> 23:11.992
Why would she ever come here?

23:12.794 --> 23:14.397
I don't believe
she's ever been to London.

23:15.233 --> 23:16.969
Though I suppose
she might soon come to visit

23:17.538 --> 23:18.807
to buy her wedding dress.

23:18.807 --> 23:21.679
Now, this is yours to keep.

23:23.583 --> 23:25.419
Mr. Wemmick, what wedding dress
you're talking about?

23:25.954 --> 23:28.092
Miss Estella is due to marry.
It's all arranged.

23:28.092 --> 23:30.229
I just completed due diligence
on her future husband.

23:30.229 --> 23:33.001
And he... He is a very,
very respectable gentleman.

23:33.736 --> 23:35.873
Made his money
from the import of nutmeg.

23:38.546 --> 23:40.148
Will this fucking day never end?

23:41.017 --> 23:41.952
Behold, Pip.

23:42.788 --> 23:43.723
Your new home.

23:45.092 --> 23:45.994
There. There.

23:51.071 --> 23:54.578
Yeah. The, uh, pipe from here
to the river is ruptured.

23:56.682 --> 23:57.717
It is on my list.

23:59.220 --> 24:00.623
It's a long list.

24:00.957 --> 24:02.159
One of many lists.

24:02.494 --> 24:04.898
Pip, I have a list of lists.

24:06.234 --> 24:07.236
Come on.

24:08.205 --> 24:09.508
Oh, mind that.

24:13.649 --> 24:16.054
Pip Gargery, you made it.

24:18.258 --> 24:19.995
It's me. Herbert.

24:19.995 --> 24:21.699
Good God, the boy
from the brewery.

24:22.934 --> 24:23.903
What the hell is he doing here?

24:23.903 --> 24:24.905
You know him?

24:26.241 --> 24:27.510
Yes, I'm afraid I do.

24:28.311 --> 24:29.514
HERBERT: Well, come on in.

24:30.015 --> 24:31.184
I even have butter
for the toast.

24:35.125 --> 24:37.129
(PANTING)

24:38.599 --> 24:39.534
(EXHALES)

24:40.837 --> 24:41.973
I could hardly sleep
knowing you were coming.

24:41.973 --> 24:42.941
Yeah.

24:43.743 --> 24:44.644
Come in!

