32:55.660 --> 32:56.661
GUARD: Compeyson.

32:58.131 --> 33:00.301
What did you do to that man
that was so wrong?

33:01.538 --> 33:03.474
It was an affair
that started with a girl.

33:04.644 --> 33:06.180
And now a boy.

33:08.117 --> 33:10.221
It is the boy
who I am traveling to see.

33:18.371 --> 33:19.574
Don't spare the horses.

33:21.377 --> 33:24.316
(CHICKENS CLUCKING)

33:39.413 --> 33:40.248
PIP: <i>My dearest Biddy,</i>

33:41.685 --> 33:43.288
<i>it is now two weeks
since I left home,</i>

33:43.288 --> 33:44.724
<i>and all is going splendidly.</i>

33:46.260 --> 33:48.164
<i>And London is not the place
I imagined it would be.</i>

33:49.100 --> 33:51.538
BIDDY: <i>"London is bigger,
wilder, madder</i>

33:51.538 --> 33:53.375
<i>"and more beautiful
than anything</i>

33:53.375 --> 33:55.112
<i>"that can ever be written down.</i>

33:55.112 --> 33:57.115
<i>"And so, I will not even
try to express it."</i>

34:01.658 --> 34:05.231
"My guardian, Daggers..."

34:07.570 --> 34:09.339
Actually I think it's "Jaggers".

34:09.574 --> 34:10.609
It says,

34:10.609 --> 34:15.285
"Mr. Jaggers has put me
to work in the counting...

34:15.285 --> 34:17.389
"Counting houses of London."

34:17.389 --> 34:18.793
Pip is in the counting house

34:18.793 --> 34:20.361
counting out his money
with the King.

34:21.832 --> 34:24.771
Like in the nursery rhyme
with the maid and the blackbird.

34:24.771 --> 34:26.542
Joe, we don't have a king,
we have a queen.

34:26.542 --> 34:28.612
But then who is Pip
in the counting house with?

34:31.618 --> 34:33.522
PIP: <i>I'm conducting business
in the counting houses</i>

34:33.522 --> 34:34.489
<i>with Herbert Pocket.</i>

34:35.425 --> 34:36.829
<i>In the exchanges,</i>

34:36.829 --> 34:38.665
<i>I am becoming the more
well-known of the two of us.</i>

34:39.199 --> 34:40.570
<i>And I have found
I have an affinity</i>

34:40.570 --> 34:42.272
<i>for brokerage
and ship insurance.</i>

34:43.074 --> 34:45.145
"I am learning
to weigh and measure

34:45.145 --> 34:46.313
"and count and assign.

34:47.149 --> 34:49.286
"I helped judge
the fitness of ships to sail.

34:49.755 --> 34:50.857
"A difficult task made easier

34:50.857 --> 34:53.427
"by all the time I used to spend
at my bedroom window..."

34:54.129 --> 34:55.398
What on Earth did he do
at his bedroom window?

34:56.300 --> 34:58.304
"...where I used to gaze out
over the Thames

34:58.304 --> 35:00.409
"and watch and record
all the ships

35:00.409 --> 35:02.446
"that came and went
to serve our mighty empire."

35:02.446 --> 35:03.815
Oh, how he loves the empire.

35:07.456 --> 35:09.293
"I used to write down
the names of the ships

35:09.293 --> 35:10.729
"and their size
and seaworthiness.

35:11.330 --> 35:13.267
"I see the same names
on the inventories.

35:13.669 --> 35:14.871
"Mr. Jaggers is quite astonished

35:14.871 --> 35:16.473
"at my knowledge
of Thames traffic.

35:17.142 --> 35:18.712
"So, perhaps all those years
were not wasted after all.

35:19.948 --> 35:22.185
"But now, Miss Havisham,
to a more somber matter.

35:23.221 --> 35:24.724
"It is something that weighs
heavily on my heart.

35:25.493 --> 35:27.162
"In fact, a weight
beyond measure

35:28.131 --> 35:30.569
"I heard from Mr. Jaggers'
assistant, Mr. Wemmick, that..."

35:32.774 --> 35:33.709
Go on.

35:39.521 --> 35:41.391
"I heard from Mr. Jaggers'
assistant, Mr. Wemmick,

35:41.391 --> 35:43.829
"that Estella is
very soon due to be married..."

35:45.633 --> 35:46.769
There was no point
troubling you with it

35:46.769 --> 35:47.870
until it had all been confirmed.

35:50.843 --> 35:52.814
"...married to a very
respectable gentleman."

35:52.814 --> 35:54.216
And so he is.

35:54.216 --> 35:56.588
The gentleman is
indeed very respectable.

36:00.496 --> 36:01.363
What's the matter?

36:03.702 --> 36:05.238
Haven't you always said
you wanted nothing more

36:05.238 --> 36:06.407
than a wealthy gentleman
to come along

36:06.407 --> 36:07.677
and take you off to Cairo
or somewhere?

36:07.677 --> 36:10.214
Am I allowed to know who this
very respectable gentleman is?

36:11.283 --> 36:12.754
Or do I meet him first
at the altar?

36:12.754 --> 36:15.793
Do you know, your generation
are so supremely ungrateful.

36:15.793 --> 36:17.764
I deliver a man dripping in gold

36:17.764 --> 36:19.300
- and nutmeg...
- Nutmeg?

36:19.300 --> 36:20.837
Yes, He made half
his money from nutmeg.

36:20.837 --> 36:22.507
- I hate nutmeg.
- And now I have

36:22.507 --> 36:24.578
all the bona fides
and the financial confirmations

36:24.578 --> 36:25.980
as to the state
of his company affairs,

36:25.980 --> 36:27.382
the wedding can take place.

36:29.419 --> 36:31.424
How dare you presume...

36:31.424 --> 36:32.660
Do I need to remind you?

36:34.396 --> 36:35.700
If it weren't for me
pulling you up

36:35.700 --> 36:37.236
from the running gutters
of Lewisham,

36:37.236 --> 36:38.639
you would be selling
your pretty ass

36:38.639 --> 36:41.343
for two shillings a time,
five times a night.

36:42.947 --> 36:45.686
As it is, you will sell yourself
just the once,

36:45.686 --> 36:47.523
for an income of £200 a year.

36:48.859 --> 36:49.761
You will travel to London

36:49.761 --> 36:51.732
and you will smell
the money and the nutmeg

36:51.732 --> 36:52.867
and you will tarry
just long enough

36:52.867 --> 36:54.269
to try your wedding dress!

36:55.639 --> 36:57.811
I do this,
I do all of this to ensure

36:57.811 --> 37:00.549
that you wear your wedding dress
for just one day!

37:01.483 --> 37:03.420
And I shall be buried in mine.

37:05.526 --> 37:08.765
Girls of your birth
really don't have choices.

