39:16.220 --> 39:17.189
What's good about him?

39:17.189 --> 39:18.692
First of all, is that
he is a quick learner.

39:19.861 --> 39:21.096
- And second of all...
- (SNEEZES)

39:26.140 --> 39:28.144
Second of all,
he has no religion

39:28.144 --> 39:29.714
to get in the way
of my instruction.

39:30.048 --> 39:31.149
Hmm?

39:32.620 --> 39:35.124
And third of all,
he understands the river.

39:35.693 --> 39:37.428
He grew up in its banks.

39:38.230 --> 39:39.601
He knows the ships
like a directory

39:39.601 --> 39:41.137
and when it suits him,

39:41.137 --> 39:43.474
he speaks the dialect of the men
who sail them.

39:44.109 --> 39:45.011
A common boy.

39:46.046 --> 39:46.914
With ambition.

39:47.583 --> 39:48.785
If he's so good,

39:49.219 --> 39:51.123
why are you trying
to sell him to me?

39:52.660 --> 39:54.429
I'm not selling him,
I'm renting him.

39:55.799 --> 39:57.169
I have decided to go

39:57.169 --> 39:58.939
into the marine
insurance business.

39:58.939 --> 40:01.109
(SNICKERS)

40:03.915 --> 40:05.886
Then the Royal Navy fleet
must be on guard

40:05.886 --> 40:08.224
for unexpected holes
below the water line.

40:08.224 --> 40:10.161
The boy is my bridge
into the business.

40:10.161 --> 40:12.666
And you chose me as a broker
because I am the best.

40:15.004 --> 40:16.941
In the sense that you are
the worst, yes.

40:18.144 --> 40:19.914
Just as I am the worst attorney.

40:20.816 --> 40:21.751
In the moral sense.

40:24.957 --> 40:26.728
What is your
immoral proposition?

40:27.262 --> 40:29.166
For the majority of underwriters
in this city,

40:29.166 --> 40:32.171
the most obnoxious problem
is fraudulent policy claims.

40:33.575 --> 40:34.610
Indeed.

40:35.211 --> 40:36.681
My proposition

40:37.617 --> 40:40.055
is that you and I will only
underwrite insurance policies

40:40.055 --> 40:41.924
we already know
to be fraudulent.

40:42.325 --> 40:43.495
(CLEARS THROAT)

40:44.029 --> 40:46.033
(SNIFFING)

40:47.102 --> 40:47.970
Why would we do that?

40:53.615 --> 40:55.786
Because if a voyage ends
in shipwreck,

40:57.623 --> 40:59.092
under a fraudulent policy,

40:59.627 --> 41:01.531
I can always use
my abilities in court

41:01.531 --> 41:02.933
to deny the claim.

41:03.835 --> 41:05.505
My point being,

41:06.373 --> 41:10.047
if we only ever underwrite
deniable claims,

41:10.883 --> 41:13.955
then you will never pay out
on a policy ever again.

41:16.594 --> 41:18.832
How on Earth would
we know in advance

41:18.832 --> 41:21.738
that a policy we are
underwriting is fraudulent?

41:28.184 --> 41:30.822
In around ten seconds,
you will find out.

41:35.999 --> 41:37.235
(WATCH TICKING)

41:38.638 --> 41:39.573
Three...

41:44.917 --> 41:45.852
Two...

41:52.332 --> 41:53.635
One.

41:53.635 --> 41:55.772
- (KNOCK ON DOOR)
- Come.

42:01.183 --> 42:02.251
Pip, Drummle. Drummle, Pip.

42:03.320 --> 42:04.289
Good morning, Mr. Drummle.

42:05.659 --> 42:06.961
And a very good morning to you.

42:07.362 --> 42:08.297
Snuff?

42:09.901 --> 42:11.003
I don't.

42:11.003 --> 42:13.240
Well, do.

42:16.180 --> 42:17.148
I just told you.

42:18.852 --> 42:19.787
I don't.

42:22.693 --> 42:23.628
Bravo.

42:27.335 --> 42:28.270
Sit.

42:31.210 --> 42:33.013
Please do, take a seat.

42:41.363 --> 42:42.633
I rowed out
to the former East Indiaman

42:42.633 --> 42:43.635
of the Black Ball Line,

42:43.635 --> 42:44.904
anchored at London Bridge
as you instructed.

42:45.940 --> 42:47.910
And aboard, you got
to talking to the captain

42:47.910 --> 42:48.812
in the captain's cabin.

42:49.680 --> 42:50.615
Yes.

42:52.953 --> 42:54.189
It is a very interesting ship.

42:55.225 --> 42:58.631
It was built at £40 a ton.
She's 1,200 tons.

42:59.700 --> 43:01.671
Her ratio beam to length is
five and a half to one,

43:01.671 --> 43:03.207
which is the new
American dimension.

43:03.207 --> 43:05.378
Designed in Boston, and...

43:05.378 --> 43:07.348
Who the fuck discusses
beams and lengths?

43:08.284 --> 43:09.185
I do.

43:11.724 --> 43:12.659
As I told the captain,

43:13.528 --> 43:15.398
ships and their design
is my interest.

43:15.398 --> 43:16.366
Hmm.

43:19.707 --> 43:20.642
Well, it is.

43:26.854 --> 43:28.390
He took out some drawings
of the ship to show me.

43:30.996 --> 43:31.931
I was impressed.

43:34.402 --> 43:35.972
I asked after his destination.

43:38.010 --> 43:40.114
And then you asked about
the cargo as I told you to.

43:44.055 --> 43:45.391
Wedgwood porcelain,

43:45.793 --> 43:47.830
silks of beams

43:50.869 --> 43:52.238
and three quarters of a ton
of illicit gunpowder.

43:57.282 --> 43:58.350
The captain
told you this himself?

44:00.822 --> 44:02.960
Picture the scene, Mr. Drummle.

44:04.162 --> 44:07.101
Pip sat there
on the couch, sweetly.

44:07.970 --> 44:09.840
The captain wanting
to play the rogue.

44:13.213 --> 44:15.117
He said if I didn't believe him,
he would show me below.

44:17.790 --> 44:18.725
Go on, Pip.

44:22.065 --> 44:23.367
I went below
and saw the powder for myself.

44:25.839 --> 44:26.741
And then...

44:30.047 --> 44:31.383
He led me to the shadows

44:31.952 --> 44:33.321
and asked if I wanted
to sail with him

44:33.321 --> 44:34.255
and share his quarters.

44:35.458 --> 44:36.861
Just as far as Liverpool.

44:37.830 --> 44:39.432
He said he would pay
for my passage back to London.

44:44.109 --> 44:45.077
He tried to hold me.

44:46.113 --> 44:47.014
Luckily, I'm strong.

44:48.852 --> 44:50.187
I went back onto the deck
and rowed to shore.

44:51.189 --> 44:53.427
With your valuable knowledge
secure in your head.

44:54.530 --> 44:55.431
You see, Drummle,

44:56.267 --> 44:58.471
when Pip was first put
into my charge,

44:58.471 --> 44:59.773
I wondered to myself,

45:00.441 --> 45:03.280
"How can a man like me
make use of such innocence?"

45:03.782 --> 45:06.921
But make use of it
you surely have.

45:06.921 --> 45:09.058
MR. JAGGERS: The boy
will hear many things.

45:09.593 --> 45:11.263
Because who among us
does not want

45:11.263 --> 45:13.433
to impress the impressionable?

45:14.068 --> 45:16.039
A captain running gunpowder
to New York?

45:17.375 --> 45:18.243
He would hang.

45:19.179 --> 45:21.249
But blackmail...

45:22.418 --> 45:25.792
It is too crude for gentlemen
such as us, Mr. Drummle.

45:27.997 --> 45:29.934
The letter I had Pip
deliver to the captain

45:29.934 --> 45:32.339
was a recommendation that he
should have his ship insured

45:32.339 --> 45:33.942
for the journey to Liverpool
and New York

45:33.942 --> 45:35.477
by Drummle Underwriters...

45:36.246 --> 45:37.281
at premium.

45:37.281 --> 45:40.823
A double premium policy
which we know in advance,

45:40.823 --> 45:42.560
can never be claimed against.

45:42.560 --> 45:44.262
MR. JAGGERS: Because I have
a rat in the river.

45:45.866 --> 45:47.001
And should the claim
ever come to court,

45:47.402 --> 45:49.106
Pip would be our witness

45:49.106 --> 45:51.510
that the ship was carrying
a dangerous and illegal cargo,

45:52.244 --> 45:54.550
which he saw
with his own two eyes.

45:54.550 --> 45:56.219
Innocent as an oyster knife.

45:58.625 --> 46:00.963
Mr. Jaggers, may I welcome you
to the world of marine commerce

46:00.963 --> 46:02.064
with open arms?

46:03.067 --> 46:04.169
MR. JAGGERS: And may I suggest

46:04.169 --> 46:06.106
that if our
relationship prospers,

46:06.575 --> 46:08.177
you will make
more money from this

46:08.177 --> 46:10.815
than you ever did
from the importation of nutmeg.

46:11.116 --> 46:11.984
(MR. DRUMMLE CHUCKLES)

46:15.959 --> 46:18.296
May I also welcome you, Pip,

46:20.034 --> 46:23.440
to Her Majesty's Royal Exchange
in all its glory.

46:39.540 --> 46:40.542
PIP: That man imports nutmeg?

46:42.546 --> 46:44.817
He made half
of his fortune from it.

46:46.219 --> 46:47.556
And let me guess,
he's soon to be married?

46:48.658 --> 46:50.094
Indeed, he is.

46:51.329 --> 46:52.298
Mr. Jaggers.

46:53.200 --> 46:54.135
Mr. Jaggers.

46:55.605 --> 46:57.342
You just deliberately
introduced me to the man

46:57.342 --> 46:58.911
who is planning to marry
the woman I love.

47:02.118 --> 47:03.921
Indeed, I did. Yes.

47:05.592 --> 47:07.162
Other than the fact
that you are evil

47:07.162 --> 47:09.132
and celebrated for it,
what is your reason?

47:11.504 --> 47:12.907
And what did you know
about that captain

47:12.907 --> 47:14.075
before you sent me to his ship?

47:20.922 --> 47:21.924
Pip,

47:22.993 --> 47:24.597
let us find
a more suitable place

47:24.597 --> 47:26.299
for what really ought
to be a celebration.

47:32.178 --> 47:33.113
(EXHALES)

47:35.284 --> 47:37.388
- (CHEERFUL MUSIC PLAYING)
- (INDISTINCT CHATTER)

47:48.177 --> 47:50.314
What exactly is it that we are
celebrating, Mr. Jaggers?

47:51.684 --> 47:53.453
We are celebrating the fact

47:53.855 --> 47:55.324
that you and I, Pip,

47:55.926 --> 47:58.631
are going to enter Drummle's
marine insurance business

47:59.032 --> 48:01.169
on a tidal wave
of his own greed.

48:02.205 --> 48:03.975
Once inside, we will eat it,

48:05.077 --> 48:06.346
digest it,

48:07.148 --> 48:09.252
then shit it out
at the other end, for profit.

48:12.058 --> 48:14.095
I said first, I would
turn you into a rat.

48:14.564 --> 48:15.999
That is now underway.

48:17.068 --> 48:19.071
Next, a snake.

48:20.341 --> 48:22.044
Betraying your business partner.

48:23.080 --> 48:24.348
BOTH: Then a vulture.

48:26.621 --> 48:29.125
We will turn your £5,000

48:29.727 --> 48:31.162
into £50,000,

48:32.098 --> 48:33.534
then £100,000.

48:35.739 --> 48:37.175
We will use my money?

48:37.175 --> 48:39.111
We are not using your money.

48:39.747 --> 48:41.149
We are investing it.

48:42.619 --> 48:44.723
For surety, I will match it
from my own pocket.

48:48.096 --> 48:49.398
Break the ice, Pip.

49:08.403 --> 49:09.973
- (MUSIC STOPS)
- (CHATTERING STOPS)

49:14.449 --> 49:15.350
MR. JAGGERS: Carry on.

49:18.825 --> 49:20.327
Put the pieces in the bucket.

49:30.414 --> 49:33.688
When you have £100,000,

49:35.190 --> 49:37.362
then, perhaps your desire
to be a gentleman

49:37.362 --> 49:38.363
will be fulfilled.

49:39.700 --> 49:41.469
And once you are a gentleman,

49:42.204 --> 49:45.545
the whole almighty
British Empire

49:45.545 --> 49:49.218
will be spread before your feet
like the skin of a tiger.

49:52.693 --> 49:55.264
Of course, you know
that I have another desire.

49:55.264 --> 49:56.266
(MR. JAGGERS CHUCKLES)

49:57.769 --> 49:58.772
Estella.

49:58.772 --> 49:59.773
Yes.

50:02.278 --> 50:05.050
And if you help ruin
Drummle's business,

50:05.719 --> 50:08.189
Estella might be freed
from her affiancement.

50:12.365 --> 50:14.168
So, you are giving me
two motivations.

50:15.672 --> 50:16.707
Avarice...

50:17.843 --> 50:19.078
and love.

50:20.247 --> 50:21.717
Two fine horses
to pull a heavy carriage.

50:27.328 --> 50:29.099
It was I who
recommended Drummle

50:29.099 --> 50:30.368
to Miss Havisham

50:30.368 --> 50:32.105
as Estella's future husband,

50:32.105 --> 50:34.308
so that he might serve
this very purpose.

50:41.423 --> 50:44.428
You spend a great deal of time
on your strategies.

50:46.600 --> 50:47.669
I sleep very little.

50:52.244 --> 50:53.346
Will you join me, Pip?

50:55.552 --> 50:56.620
My head is still spinning.

50:57.556 --> 50:59.760
MR. JAGGERS: In pursuit
of avarice and love,

51:00.662 --> 51:02.632
no matter what crime you commit,

51:03.801 --> 51:05.838
I am the best lawyer in London.

51:07.475 --> 51:11.517
And I will always find a way
to have all charges dropped.

51:15.658 --> 51:17.161
Put the champagne on ice, Pip.

51:27.649 --> 51:29.151
Now, pick up your glass.

51:31.590 --> 51:32.525
Come on.

51:41.711 --> 51:45.384
To liberty, love and money.

51:46.220 --> 51:48.892
In any order of priority
you wish to put them.

51:48.892 --> 51:49.826
(GLASSES CLINK)

52:02.218 --> 52:02.919
(PIP EXHALES HEAVILY)

52:04.990 --> 52:07.796
Pip, that gentleman over there
is very well-connected

52:07.796 --> 52:09.766
with the finest ladies
in Wapping.

52:11.837 --> 52:13.942
If you accompany him upstairs,

52:13.942 --> 52:15.377
you will get to meet
some of them.

52:16.714 --> 52:17.882
And you can take your pick.

52:23.995 --> 52:24.930
(COINS JINGLING)

52:25.665 --> 52:26.567
Hello, handsome.

52:27.268 --> 52:28.203
(KISSING)

52:30.340 --> 52:31.577
I want to go home and...

52:32.478 --> 52:33.413
and think about everything.

52:39.459 --> 52:40.495
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

52:41.329 --> 52:42.398
Go on.

52:43.100 --> 52:45.605
And if I see you
at the exchange tomorrow,

52:45.605 --> 52:46.940
I will know I've got a partner.

53:34.001 --> 53:35.938
(BIRDS CAWING)

53:41.382 --> 53:43.319
(WATER SPLASHING)

54:36.694 --> 54:37.996
(DOOR OPENS)

54:40.067 --> 54:41.069
(DOOR CLOSES)

54:41.069 --> 54:42.304
Pip.

54:43.841 --> 54:44.843
Pip?

54:46.446 --> 54:48.851
Pip, I... I've had a letter
from Miss Havisham.

54:50.655 --> 54:51.590
Estella.

54:51.991 --> 54:52.859
She's coming to London.

54:56.065 --> 54:57.502
When?

54:57.502 --> 54:59.405
Uh, the letter didn't say.
But she's coming.

55:04.983 --> 55:06.620
I hear Miss Havisham
has found her a suitor.

55:11.597 --> 55:13.466
Which one of us do you think
it is she will marry?

55:25.023 --> 55:26.927
(INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)
